BAUCHI – Bauchi State Motorcycles Dealers and Sellers Association has vowed to purchase intent and nomination forms for All Progressives Congress (APC) gubernatorial aspirant Al’ameen Sani Muhammad. The State Chairman of the Association, Alhaji Muazu Ciroma who stated this on Friday while speaking with reporters said that the association and other associations of like minds have contributed N36,000,000 to buy the governorship forms for the aspirant. He said that the group’s clamour for Al’ameen Mohammed is to enable him to replicate the outstanding feat he has achieved as one of the strong political pillars in the state. He reiterated the group’s determination to use the mobilise funds to purchase the gubernatorial nomination form for Al’ameen because “he is an exemplary leader.” “He refused to participate in the past administration’s in the state, despite being in active Politics, various groups are satisfied with his exemplary leadership qualities, they are threatening to organised a protest to pressurize him to declare his intention to contest. “We intervened and we met his close associates, family, friends and relatives because he came from a respected family, and they pledged to us that he will contest , we stopped the various youths group from the protest or taking him to court because of fasting period but after eidel fitr celebration, he will declare his interest, I assure you,” he said. The Chairman who was one of the die hard supporter of the incumbent Bauchi State Governor, Senator Bala Mohammed, said that since Bala Mohammed is contesting for President, they now picked Al’ameen as their gubernatorial aspirant in the state in any political party of his choice. He also said that they are confident that Al’ameen has all it takes to govern the state if given a chance, and he will change the narratives in all aspect of life. POLL He described Al’ameen as a charismatic leader patriot ,philanthropist, an elder statesman who is always committed to ensure justice and fairness in his dealings with anyone in Nigeria.